  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study will examine how safe and effective apricitabine is when given long term (as
      ongoing treatment) to HIV patients who have already completed the AVX-201 trial
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      An ongoing study (AVX-201) is examining the safety and efficacy of apricitabine compared to
      3TC in HIV patients who are failing therapy containing 3TC and have the presence of the M184V
      mutation in reverse transcriptase. This extension study (AVX-201E) is available to patients
      who complete the AVX-201 protocol.

      Patients will continue to receive apricitabine open label for a further 96 weeks (making a
      total of 144 weeks from starting AVX-201) in addition to an optimised background. Safety
      markers and efficacy markers will be followed.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
